    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES FS-5106 AND FS-6206 - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT AND REVERSE IDLER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT AND REVERSE IDLER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts and remove the countershaft rear bearing cover and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300816">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300816" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300816" filename="../figg13/G1300816.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two set screws (inset,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300817">Figure 4.15</hotlnk>). Remove bearing retainer, outer race and shims.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300817" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300817" filename="../figg13/G1300817.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Set Screws, Bearing Retainer, Outer Race and Shims</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Countershaft may slide to the rear and out of bearing bore.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a slide hammer to remove the reverse idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300818">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Remove locating ball once it is exposed (inset).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300818" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300818" filename="../figg13/G1300818.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse idler, bearings, spacer and thrust washers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300819">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300819" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300819" filename="../figg13/G1300819.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Reverse Idler, Bearings, Spacer and Thrust Washers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft assembly to the rear and lift it from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300820">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300820" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300820" filename="../figg13/G1300820.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Lift Countershaft Assembly From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the countershaft front bearing race is to be replaced, drive the bore plug through the
                front of the transmission and drive the race to the rear toward the inside of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300821">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300821" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300821" filename="../figg13/G1300821.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Drive Bore Plug Through Front of Transmission</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
